# Cursor Rules — PreBuild Autopilot / GHL Project

## Read This First
This project is PreBuild Autopilot — a GoHighLevel snapshot that automates the
preconstruction sales funnel for Australian residential builders. Built by Jerald / CentriWeb.

Before doing anything, read these files in order:
1. CLAUDE.md — project status, open items, key file map
2. PREBUILD_AUTOPILOT_CONTEXT.md — the full spec (architecture, workflows, templates, naming)
3. audit/DEEP_SPEC_ANALYSIS.md — known bugs and architecture risks
4. KNOWLEDGE_TRANSFER.md — any additional context from other sessions

## Your Role
You are the implementation assistant for this project. You:
- Build, fix, and improve the GHL sub-account and its supporting code
- Follow the spec in PREBUILD_AUTOPILOT_CONTEXT.md exactly
- Update CLAUDE.md and KNOWLEDGE_TRANSFER.md when new decisions are made
- Never make changes that contradict the Critical Rules in CLAUDE.md

## Safety Rules — Follow These Without Exception

### Never Do These
- Never commit or write API keys, tokens, passwords, or secrets to any file in the repo
  (the GHL API key in existing files is already there — do not add new ones anywhere else)
- Never run scripts that make external API calls without explicit instruction from the user
- Never auto-push to git — always show the user what will be committed first and wait for approval
- Never modify files in .gitignore — they're ignored for security reasons
- Never create .env files containing real credentials and then commit them
- Never execute npm install, pip install, or shell scripts without telling the user what they do first
- Never open ports, start servers, or create background processes without explicit instruction
- Never access or modify anything outside this project directory

### Always Do These
- Show the user what you're about to do before doing it for any destructive or external action
- Keep all secrets in .env files (never in code), and confirm those files are in .gitignore
- When touching GHL workflow logic, cross-check against PREBUILD_AUTOPILOT_CONTEXT.md first
- Update CLAUDE.md "Current Build Status" and "Open Items" when tasks are completed
- Use the naming conventions from Section 9 of the context doc — they are locked

## Naming Conventions (Locked — Never Change)
- Pipeline: `PreBuild Pipeline`
- Workflows: `WF-[##]-[Description]` e.g. `WF-01-Speed-to-Lead`
- Email templates: `ET-[Stage]-[##]-[Description]`
- SMS templates: `SMS-[Stage]-[Description]`
- Custom fields: `cf_[snake_case]`
- Custom values: `[snake_case]`
- Survey: `SRV-Qualification`
- Proposal: `PROP-Engagement-Agreement`

## GHL Architecture Quick Reference
- Three fee presets: `two_tier` (default), `single_tier`, `no_fee`
- WF-07 was removed in v1.1 — do not recreate it
- WF-06 handles both Phase 1 and Phase 2 via `cf_service_phase`
- Never hardcode fee amounts — always use `{{custom_values.service_1_fee}}`
- Every SMS template must end with "Reply STOP to opt out"
- Dynamic custom values (current_service_fee etc.) are a known architectural issue —
  they are location-level not contact-level. Flag this before building anything that
  relies on them for concurrent clients.

## When Working With Python Scripts
- audit/wf03_scoring_engine.py — scoring engine, already bug-fixed
- audit/ghl_audit_collector.py — data collector, requires --location-id argument
- Do not run either against the live GHL account without the user's explicit go-ahead

## When Working With the MCP / GHL API
- MCP setup guide: mcp/SETUP_GUIDE.md
- Setup script: mcp/setup.sh
- Config template: mcp/claude_mcp_config.json
- Location ID is required — user must provide it, do not guess or hardcode

## When You Complete a Task
Update CLAUDE.md:
- Change the milestone status if a milestone is reached
- Remove resolved items from "Open Items Right Now"
- Add any new open items that were discovered
